summary: I am a student with passion for making difference in the world. I believe that the world is always changing and moving forward and requires motivated people to help lead the way. I enjoy investing my time into amazing opportunities that helps me to grow as a professional and as a person while helping to create opportunities and benefits for others. I believe that it is important to invest in the resources you have as well as to invest your time in an organization even if that meant not benefiting from it at all.

experience.title: Volunteer EMT
experience.description: Certified as Emergency Medical Technician (EMT-B); CPR by American Heart Association Healthcare Provider level; First Aid and other EMT-B protocol per state/squad; ambulance checks; ensure supplies; assist in patient care at scene, enroute, and hospital until transfer; write call sheet; maintain coverage; operate electronic charting system; completed EMT class, CEVO course, and ICS-100/200/700; provide medical transport as dispatched; able to lift >50 lbs; ensure ambulance is stocked; training with Captain; incident reports; patient assessments; emergency transport decisions; notify dispatch for lights/sirens; timely transports; retrieve paperwork; track times and mileage; shift start/end radio and transport sheet handling.

experience.title: Volunteer EMT
experience.description: Providing medical transport for patient as requested by dispatch; lift >50 lbs; ambulance stock checks; training with Captain; incident reporting; patient assessments during pick-up, transport, and arrival; emergency transport decisions; notify dispatch of situation for lights/sirens; timely transports; paperwork and transport sheet management.

experience.title: Retail Sales Associate
experience.description: Providing excellent customer service; understanding department products; meeting daily sales goals; maintaining the sales floor; opening Macy's Star Rewards Credit Card for customers; meeting department managers' expectations; attending scheduled training classes.

experience.title: Assistant Martial Arts Instructor
experience.description: Assisting the instructor in managing classes; guiding students; managing classes of different belt levels, ages, and sizes; reported to Head Instructor/Master/Instructor; assisting in setup, management, and cleanup of student promotion exams.
